From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Update runnable_weight in set/clear_delayed()

When a task entity is delay-dequeued, set_delayed() walks every
ancestor cfs_rq and decrements h_nr_runnable. However, it never
calls se_update_runnable() for the ancestor group entities, leaving
their runnable_weight stale.

Since dequeue_entities() returns -1 for delayed tasks (skipping the
second for_each_sched_entity loop that normally calls
se_update_runnable), and entity_tick() also omits it, the stale
runnable_weight feeds into PELT via se_runnable() across multiple
ticks until the next enqueue/dequeue event corrects it.

Fix this by calling se_update_runnable() inside the
for_each_sched_entity loops in both set_delayed() and
clear_delayed(). For task entities the call is a no-op; for group
entities it syncs runnable_weight with the just-modified
h_nr_runnable.

Fixes: 3429dd57f0de ("sched/fair: Fix inaccurate h_nr_runnable accounting with delayed dequeue")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@kernel.org>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index 8ce56a8d507f..1234567890ab 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -5314,6 +5314,7 @@ static void set_delayed(struct sched_entity *se)
 		struct cfs_rq *cfs_rq = cfs_rq_of(se);
 
 		cfs_rq->h_nr_runnable--;
+		se_update_runnable(se);
 	}
 }
 
@@ -5334,6 +5335,7 @@ static void clear_delayed(struct sched_entity *se)
 		struct cfs_rq *cfs_rq = cfs_rq_of(se);
 
 		cfs_rq->h_nr_runnable++;
+		se_update_runnable(se);
 	}
 }
 
